00:00:01.034 --> 00:00:03.069 line:5%,start
ABBY (VOICEOVER):
Previously on "Dance Moms."

00:00:03.136 --> 00:00:06.139 line:5%,start
ABBY: All of you have the
opportunity to come and see me
in LA.

00:00:06.206 --> 00:00:07.774 line:5%,start
Maddie came out.

00:00:07.974 --> 00:00:10.477 line:5%,start
KELLY: She's going to die
alone with no friends.

00:00:10.543 --> 00:00:12.312 line:5%,start
I'm sure you wish I would
die in a car accident too.

00:00:12.712 --> 00:00:15.648 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: You saw how much time
she spent on Maddie and
Mackenzie.

00:00:15.749 --> 00:00:17.584 line:5%,start
Chloe didn't even
learn her dance.

00:00:17.717 --> 00:00:20.420 line:5%,start
ANNOUNCER: First runner
up is Miss Maddie.

00:00:20.587 --> 00:00:22.389 line:5%,start
-She was crying.
-Thank you.

00:00:22.655 --> 00:00:26.192 line:5%,start
Screw you! You know what?
You're always against me.

00:00:26.259 --> 00:00:28.294 line:5%,start
I'm done. I'm so over it.

00:00:29.662 --> 00:00:31.031 line:5%,start
ABBY (VOICEOVER): Coming
up on "Dance Moms."

00:00:31.131 --> 00:00:34.801 line:5%,start
ABBY: This week, you will be
performing in the annual dance
concert.

00:00:35.535 --> 00:00:39.072 line:5%,start
Now, something else is going on.
We're going to throw in a photo
shoot.

00:00:39.272 --> 00:00:40.640 line:5%,start
Shush the beak.

00:00:40.707 --> 00:00:43.243 line:5%,start
Stop it. Since when does
your ass go on my stage?

00:00:43.777 --> 00:00:46.312 line:5%,start
If you think Christi and Kelly
are going to make your kid a
star,

00:00:46.613 --> 00:00:49.682 line:5%,start
by all means, go.
Pick which side you're on.

00:00:49.816 --> 00:00:53.286 line:5%,start
KELLY: Never, in 40 years of
being in Abby Lee Dance Company

00:00:53.353 --> 00:00:57.957 line:5%,start
has anyone been given a solo
the day of the [bleep] recital?

00:00:58.058 --> 00:00:59.859 line:5%,start
ABBY: She's going to crap all
over me and talk to me that way

00:00:59.926 --> 00:01:01.628 line:5%,start
in front of my
customers? No way.

00:01:01.694 --> 00:01:04.164 line:95%,end
[theme music playing]

00:01:04.364 --> 00:01:05.665 line:95%,end
LYRICS: Get up.

00:01:05.865 --> 00:01:07.600 line:95%,end
Get on the floor.

00:01:07.834 --> 00:01:12.772 line:95%,end
My world is with my girls,
living on the dance floor.

00:01:14.140 --> 00:01:16.910 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:01:17.677 --> 00:01:18.878 line:5%,start
ABBY: Come on. Let's go!

00:01:19.112 --> 00:01:21.147 line:5%,start
This is a busy week.
We have lots to do. Let's go.

00:01:21.247 --> 00:01:24.384 line:5%,start
This week is going to be more
hectic and stressful than ever.

00:01:24.517 --> 00:01:27.854 line:5%,start
This is the week of the
Abby Lee Dance Company's

00:01:27.954 --> 00:01:29.355 line:5%,start
annual dance concert.

00:01:29.656 --> 00:01:33.359 line:95%,end
I need these kids to be focused,
because we have a lot to get
done.

00:01:33.993 --> 00:01:36.763 line:95%,end
Let's get to the pyramid.
I want to get through it
quickly.

00:01:37.097 --> 00:01:39.165 line:95%,end
We have a very, very
busy week ahead of us.

00:01:39.232 --> 00:01:41.801 line:95%,end
We were the overall
high score winning group.

00:01:41.868 --> 00:01:43.269 line:95%,end
Give yourselves a
round of applause.

00:01:43.336 --> 00:01:44.437 line:95%,end
[clapping]

00:01:44.504 --> 00:01:45.572 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:01:45.638 --> 00:01:49.542 line:95%,end
LYRICS: Beating in my heart,
choking on the darkness.

00:01:51.978 --> 00:01:53.513 line:95%,end
ABBY: Paige, you knew
that was coming, right?

00:01:54.647 --> 00:01:55.715 line:5%,start
Why?

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:02.989 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:02:03.323 --> 00:02:04.891 line:95%,end
Just like Maddie's
costume fallout?

00:02:05.158 --> 00:02:07.293 line:95%,end
Paige made a tiny mistake
in the group dance,

00:02:07.360 --> 00:02:09.329 line:95%,end
and Abby puts her at the
bottom of the pyramid.

00:02:09.395 --> 00:02:12.799 line:5%,start
Maddie's strap came off of her
apron, and she didn't even get
in trouble.

00:02:12.932 --> 00:02:14.534 line:5%,start
As a matter of fact,
Abby laughed at her.

00:02:15.368 --> 00:02:17.036 line:5%,start
LYRICS: And then
you kissed me, and--

00:02:19.939 --> 00:02:22.942 line:95%,end
LYRICS: Call me up
after a bad day of work.

00:02:23.510 --> 00:02:25.712 line:95%,end
I am tired of Abby
mistreating my kids.

00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:27.847 line:95%,end
And I'm not going to let her
do it anymore.

00:02:28.047 --> 00:02:30.150 line:95%,end
Did you forget part
of your dance? No.

00:02:30.216 --> 00:02:34.254 line:95%,end
So it was the costume falling
off, right? Paige, do you want
to be here?

00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:36.322 line:95%,end
Because your mother is still
making excuses for you.

00:02:36.389 --> 00:02:40.193 line:95%,end
No, I'm not. You made that
excuse for Maddie, so I was
making it for Paige.

00:02:40.360 --> 00:02:44.097 line:95%,end
Paige screwed up the whole group
number in front of a live
audience.

00:02:44.164 --> 00:02:45.265 line:95%,end
And we won.

00:02:45.331 --> 00:02:48.067 line:95%,end
Maddie, just drop and do 20 push
-ups. Kelly will feel better.

00:02:48.368 --> 00:02:51.037 line:95%,end
Go ahead. You're punished.
KELLY: It has nothing to do with
Maddie.

00:02:51.104 --> 00:02:52.438 line:95%,end
ABBY: You're pushed for your
costume. KELLY: I'm talking
about you.

00:02:52.605 --> 00:02:58.511 line:5%,start
Every week the moms seem to be
mad at me and Maddie for
something that's happened.

00:02:58.578 --> 00:03:02.482 line:95%,end
I'm sorry that Abby treats us
better than you guys, but it's
not my fault.

00:03:02.715 --> 00:03:03.783 line:95%,end
ABBY: Go.

00:03:04.717 --> 00:03:06.986 line:95%,end
KELLY: Maddie, please don't.
ABBY: Keep going. Go, Maddie.
Give me 20.

00:03:07.320 --> 00:03:10.356 line:95%,end
Your costume was your fault. You
should've known it was loose
backstage.

00:03:10.557 --> 00:03:13.326 line:95%,end
You should have had somebody pin
it. I am sick and tired of
fighting with Kelly.

00:03:13.426 --> 00:03:15.328 line:95%,end
This has been going
on for over a decade.

00:03:15.428 --> 00:03:18.097 line:95%,end
She brings her kids to
me to learn new things,

00:03:18.598 --> 00:03:21.734 line:95%,end
to become better dancers,
and then she fights with me.

00:03:22.235 --> 00:03:24.537 line:95%,end
You know what?
I don't care anymore, Kelly.

00:03:25.004 --> 00:03:28.841 line:95%,end
All right. Paige, you're on the
bottom of the pyramid, because
you were perfect.

00:03:29.609 --> 00:03:31.344 line:95%,end
Moving on.
[clapping]

00:03:31.411 --> 00:03:34.914 line:95%,end
Brooke, you're next, because
you were next to perfect.

00:03:35.582 --> 00:03:36.649 line:95%,end
[clapping]

00:03:36.749 --> 00:03:38.985 line:95%,end
ABBY: And now we have Kendall.

00:03:39.919 --> 00:03:43.323 line:95%,end
I saw an opening turn
that wasn't flawless.

00:03:43.923 --> 00:03:45.792 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:03:47.160 --> 00:03:49.495 line:95%,end
The rest of the
dance, you were great.

00:03:50.063 --> 00:03:52.165 line:95%,end
And next, I have Nia.


00:03:53.066 --> 00:03:55.335 line:95%,end
You never roll your eyes.
You're never upset.

00:03:55.435 --> 00:03:57.570 line:95%,end
Your mother never has to say
anything about the solos.

00:03:57.670 --> 00:03:59.339 line:95%,end
That's good, but I want more.

00:03:59.706 --> 00:04:02.075 line:95%,end
I want you to come
out and be a star.

00:04:02.475 --> 00:04:05.411 line:95%,end
And next, we have Asia.

00:04:06.379 --> 00:04:08.414 line:95%,end
Asia, you were not here
last week to perform,

00:04:08.581 --> 00:04:10.817 line:95%,end
because you were
rehearsing for a charity event.

00:04:12.085 --> 00:04:14.387 line:95%,end
ABBY: I think it's wonderful
for you to do charity events.

00:04:14.787 --> 00:04:17.290 line:95%,end
However, charity begins at home.

00:04:18.258 --> 00:04:19.659 line:95%,end
And this is now your home.

00:04:20.093 --> 00:04:23.896 line:95%,end
Really, Asia shouldn't be higher
than any of the kids

00:04:23.997 --> 00:04:25.298 line:95%,end
who performed in
the group dance.

00:04:25.365 --> 00:04:27.734 line:95%,end
Why should she get a
spot above all these kids

00:04:28.101 --> 00:04:32.905 line:95%,end
who were here over the break,
every day that they could be,
and performed for you?

00:04:32.972 --> 00:04:34.173 line:95%,end
That makes no sense.

00:04:34.274 --> 00:04:36.976 line:95%,end
KELLY: And she was training
with another-- another teacher.

00:04:37.143 --> 00:04:38.211 line:95%,end
ABBY: She was doing a--
KRISTIE: A choreographer.

00:04:38.311 --> 00:04:40.813 line:95%,end
You just told us in there
you had training all week.

00:04:41.080 --> 00:04:43.182 line:95%,end
Choreogra-- and so what--
KELLY: Training all week.

00:04:43.249 --> 00:04:44.517 line:95%,end
Let me get this straight.
Let me get this straight.

00:04:44.617 --> 00:04:47.654 line:95%,end
My daughter, whether she's here,
whether she's in a different
country,

00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:49.355 line:95%,end
she's going to train
with choreographers.

00:04:49.422 --> 00:04:50.823 line:95%,end
She's not going to have
downtime doing meet and greets.

00:04:50.890 --> 00:04:53.126 line:95%,end
OK. Then she shouldn't be
part of our team.

00:04:53.192 --> 00:04:55.662 line:95%,end
Doing meet and greets. She
should be training instead of
doing meet and greets.

00:04:55.728 --> 00:04:57.563 line:95%,end
I would love to take my
kids training somewhere else.

00:04:57.764 --> 00:04:59.899 line:95%,end
Well, then go take them to a
choreographer when you're in--

00:05:00.066 --> 00:05:02.502 line:95%,end
-instead of doing meet and
greets. -You don't understand,
we're not allowed.

00:05:02.669 --> 00:05:04.170 line:95%,end
We're not allowed.
KRISTIE: I feel bad for you.

00:05:04.270 --> 00:05:06.139 line:95%,end
-We're not allowed.
-Am I full of [bleep], moms?

00:05:06.205 --> 00:05:09.375 line:95%,end
-Please, somebody say something.
-Get over it. It just happens.

00:05:09.442 --> 00:05:12.211 line:95%,end
It happens here. It happens
there. It happens everywhere.

00:05:12.378 --> 00:05:13.479 line:95%,end
Some things never change.

00:05:13.546 --> 00:05:16.816 line:5%,start
Asia is training. She's not
sitting and playing in LA.

00:05:16.883 --> 00:05:19.419 line:95%,end
She is training with
choreographers, and I think

00:05:19.519 --> 00:05:23.389 line:95%,end
that really bothers the moms
that they kind of live in a
bubble.

00:05:23.489 --> 00:05:27.093 line:95%,end
And they don't take the
initiative and keep the girls
training on their breaks.

00:05:27.293 --> 00:05:29.996 line:95%,end
Next on the pyramid,
we have Chloe.

00:05:30.229 --> 00:05:34.434 line:95%,end
You were challenged with hip
hop. You were fourth overall
high score.

00:05:35.301 --> 00:05:38.204 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:05:40.106 --> 00:05:46.112 line:95%,end
But you need to put more effort
in. You need to be the best you
can be.

00:05:46.579 --> 00:05:47.680 line:95%,end
And I don't see that.

00:05:47.814 --> 00:05:50.783 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: Did Abby seriously say
that Chloe needed to try harder
last week?

00:05:51.117 --> 00:05:54.487 line:5%,start
Are you kidding me? Maybe you
need to offer some, I don't
know, hip hop classes.

00:05:55.955 --> 00:05:57.757 line:95%,end
Next, Maddie.

00:05:58.558 --> 00:06:00.927 line:95%,end
It kills me that you're
not on top of this pyramid,

00:06:01.427 --> 00:06:04.664 line:95%,end
because I thought that
your solo was outstanding.

00:06:04.964 --> 00:06:08.401 line:95%,end
And I was glad to see you
tapping again. But you still got
second.

00:06:09.168 --> 00:06:10.903 line:95%,end
And on top of the
pyramid is Mackenzie.

00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:12.772 line:95%,end
[clapping]

00:06:13.539 --> 00:06:16.609 line:95%,end
Mackenzie had a clean landing.
She went out on stage.

00:06:16.709 --> 00:06:18.077 line:95%,end
She did what she
was supposed to do.

00:06:18.444 --> 00:06:21.714 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: And your highest
scoring elite mini soloist is
Miss Mackenzie

00:06:21.781 --> 00:06:24.317 line:95%,end
with act number 11,
"California Adventure."

00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:26.586 line:95%,end
Congratulations,
you guys. Great job.

00:06:26.986 --> 00:06:29.989 line:95%,end
ABBY: I always say, it's tough
getting to the top,

00:06:30.089 --> 00:06:31.524 line:95%,end
but it's even tougher
staying there.

00:06:33.659 --> 00:06:34.994 line:95%,end
Turn and look to your right.

00:06:37.530 --> 00:06:39.332 line:95%,end
You going to let that girl
show up and take over?

00:06:40.733 --> 00:06:42.068 line:95%,end
That didn't look very confident.

00:06:44.670 --> 00:06:45.838 line:95%,end
Time will tell.

00:06:45.938 --> 00:06:48.307 line:95%,end
KRISTIE: Thanks for keeping
the seat warm, Kenzie, but
Asia's back,

00:06:48.374 --> 00:06:50.176 line:95%,end
and she'll be up top next week.

00:06:50.476 --> 00:06:53.045 line:95%,end
This week we are not
traveling anywhere.

00:06:53.746 --> 00:06:57.817 line:95%,end
You will be performing in
the annual dance concert.

00:06:59.152 --> 00:07:03.156 line:95%,end
Now this is a rough week for all
involved. You're going to have
quick changes.

00:07:03.322 --> 00:07:05.191 line:95%,end
You're going to have
numbers back to back.

00:07:05.324 --> 00:07:08.461 line:95%,end
You're used to lounging around
all day and getting up there for
one number.

00:07:08.761 --> 00:07:11.664 line:95%,end
Well, that ain't it,
kid. That ain't it.

00:07:11.764 --> 00:07:16.836 line:5%,start
The week of the showcase is
always the most stressful week
of the whole season.

00:07:17.069 --> 00:07:20.773 line:95%,end
So much going on, a total
of maybe 28 to 30 numbers.

00:07:21.207 --> 00:07:24.577 line:95%,end
As a parent, you can't forget
any part of the costume.

00:07:25.111 --> 00:07:29.515 line:95%,end
Kids can't forget their
choreography. It's a lot of
work-- a lot of stress.

00:07:29.849 --> 00:07:33.686 line:95%,end
Let's get to the assignments.
Everybody will be doing a solo.

00:07:34.420 --> 00:07:37.957 line:95%,end
However, most of you
will be doing old solos.

00:07:39.759 --> 00:07:43.796 line:95%,end
Paige, you have a new solo,
so the pressure is on.


00:07:44.730 --> 00:07:46.666 line:95%,end
I think that Paige
needs a new number.

00:07:46.732 --> 00:07:48.801 line:95%,end
None of Paige's solos
have really stood out.

00:07:49.602 --> 00:07:53.873 line:95%,end
So we're going to let Paige do a
new routine, and Kelly should
appreciate it,

00:07:54.040 --> 00:07:57.910 line:95%,end
because I'm taking time out of
my week to spend with her kid.

00:07:58.244 --> 00:08:01.147 line:95%,end
You will be doing a
jazz gymnastic routine.

00:08:01.948 --> 00:08:05.451 line:95%,end
So I need you totally
focused on the task at hand.

00:08:05.952 --> 00:08:09.355 line:95%,end
KELLY: Abby always complains
that Paige is like a step behind
the girls

00:08:09.422 --> 00:08:13.759 line:95%,end
in the group dances. So why
would she give her a new dance?

00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:15.862 line:95%,end
ABBY: All right. I'm going to do
something a little bit
different.

00:08:16.095 --> 00:08:18.965 line:95%,end
Brooke, I am giving you
an amazing opportunity.

00:08:19.599 --> 00:08:24.237 line:95%,end
You are going to sing your big
hit song, "Summer Love Song"
live.

00:08:24.303 --> 00:08:26.405 line:95%,end
[clapping]

00:08:27.273 --> 00:08:30.910 line:95%,end
I thought it would be a nice
treat for the audience to hear
Brooke sing

00:08:30.977 --> 00:08:35.147 line:95%,end
"Summer Love Song" live.
And Kelly should be grateful.

00:08:35.381 --> 00:08:40.786 line:95%,end
The group routine is called
Sugar Babies. I need you to hit
it hard.

00:08:40.953 --> 00:08:45.057 line:95%,end
Just in case we don't have
enough work to do the week of
our big show,

00:08:45.157 --> 00:08:46.993 line:95%,end
we're going to throw
in a photo shoot.

00:08:47.593 --> 00:08:53.165 line:95%,end
You are doing an editorial
campaign for the magazine "Dance
Track."

00:08:53.766 --> 00:08:59.438 line:95%,end
this is the first time that
"Dance Track" magazine has
interviewed kids.

00:09:00.439 --> 00:09:06.412 line:95%,end
And one is going to be chosen
for the cover of the digital
magazine.

00:09:07.613 --> 00:09:10.082 line:95%,end
Spread apart. Let's
go. Let's get working.

00:09:10.216 --> 00:09:12.785 line:95%,end
We're going to start the group
dance first so we're going to
redo the entrance.

00:09:13.486 --> 00:09:16.222 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:09:18.591 --> 00:09:22.695 line:5%,start
Girls, listen to me. Remember,
this is one of my favorite
Broadway shows.

00:09:22.762 --> 00:09:26.766 line:5%,start
Do not mess it up out there.
The group routine is Sugar
Babies.

00:09:26.933 --> 00:09:29.869 line:95%,end
It's sassy. It's fun.
They look adorable.

00:09:30.303 --> 00:09:31.637 line:95%,end
And there's some comic relief.

00:09:31.837 --> 00:09:36.008 line:95%,end
The girls come out in these
big, sloppy overcoats.

00:09:36.075 --> 00:09:37.209 line:95%,end
They look like bums.

00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:38.844 line:95%,end
[humming]
Like it's funny.

00:09:38.911 --> 00:09:40.112 line:95%,end
Put your hands on each other.

00:09:40.379 --> 00:09:43.382 line:95%,end
Like lay on each other like
you're exhausted, like you
always are anyway.

00:09:43.516 --> 00:09:46.586 line:95%,end
And they whip those overcoats
off, and underneath

00:09:46.652 --> 00:09:49.889 line:95%,end
they have white
ruffles, pink sugar.

00:09:50.323 --> 00:09:52.692 line:95%,end
It is adorable.
They look like cotton candy.

00:09:52.825 --> 00:09:57.797 line:95%,end
We have a lot to work on with
the group routine, so I don't
need any drama.

00:09:59.265 --> 00:10:02.301 line:95%,end
I just want to make sure
that I'm not losing my mind.

00:10:03.836 --> 00:10:07.039 line:95%,end
Do you guys agree with me with
the things that I said to Abby
in pyramid?

00:10:07.306 --> 00:10:09.909 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Oh, I was giving you
a preach, sista in my head.

00:10:09.976 --> 00:10:12.645 line:95%,end
OK. Because I don't want to
think that like I'm the only one

00:10:12.712 --> 00:10:13.813 line:95%,end
that thinks any of these things.

00:10:13.879 --> 00:10:15.014 line:95%,end
I was proud of you.

00:10:15.214 --> 00:10:17.583 line:95%,end
ABBY: After the way her mother
talked to me today, there is no
way

00:10:17.650 --> 00:10:19.452 line:95%,end
that kid's being in the front
in the middle of this number.

00:10:19.619 --> 00:10:23.489 line:95%,end
She always says everyone is
terrible except for Maddie and
Asia.

00:10:23.589 --> 00:10:28.861 line:95%,end
But the other five girls, she
has nothing nice to say about
those kids, ever.

00:10:28.928 --> 00:10:32.598 line:95%,end
KELLY: Nothing I said wasn't
true. I'm sick of Abby always
dumping on my kids

00:10:32.798 --> 00:10:36.736 line:95%,end
and glorifying Maddie. I'm
excited that Abby is giving
Brooke the opportunity

00:10:36.836 --> 00:10:40.272 line:95%,end
to sing at the showcase this
year, but I don't understand

00:10:40.339 --> 00:10:42.541 line:95%,end
why she's giving
Paige a new solo.

00:10:42.675 --> 00:10:45.611 line:95%,end
Like she always has to give
a negative with a positive.

